description.narrative: Due to COVID-19, Outputs 7.1 and 7.2 were re-focused on risk communication and community engagement (RCCE) in support of the COVID-19 response. While the main areas of work remained the same, the focus of UNICEF's communication and advocacy shifted to COVID-19. An integrated RCCE workplan was developed in February 2020 to build public trust in national authorities and provide a RCCE guiding framework for an effective country response. UNICEF's RCCE strategy revolves around five areas: 1. National Support and Coordination; 2. Public Awareness; 3. Community Engagement, including young people; 4. Advocacy; 5. Documentation. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:14/07/2020
